   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Seventy-two SAVED BY GRACE Scripture: Eph 2:8-9 The meaning of salvation Salvation means to be forgiven and delivered from sin.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Furthermore, salvation means to receive life and be resurrected.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Salvation also includes being ascended and transcended.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The source of salvation The grace of God is the source of salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Grace comes from love.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Grace is an active issue, and love is an intention of the heart.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>So the act of grace is an issue coming from the loving intention of the heart.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Because grace is free, salvation is not by works.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Since it is by grace and not by works, salvation is out of God and not out of ourselves.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The means of salvation Salvation is not by works, but by faith.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Grace is the dispensing; faith is the receiving.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The dispensing grace and the receiving faith make salvation complete.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The result of salvation That man may not boast in himself.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Since salvation is not by the works of man, nor out of man, there is no room for man to boast.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>That God may be man s boast and glory.</S>
   </TEXT>
